  <prompt>
    Add 3 new per-item action buttons to `NarrativeBullet` using Fluent v9 icons (`CheckmarkRegular`, `DismissRegular`, `CalendarAddRegular`). Wire the new button props through `ActivityNotesSection`. Compose the new hook handlers (from task 030) in `DailyBriefingApp.tsx` and pass them down. Preserve the existing "Add to To Do" button (4th in row, ADR-024). Verify dark-mode rendering. Update `DailyBriefingApp.smoke.test.tsx` fixtures for `sprk_briefingstate` field.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE frontend platform developer. Expert in React component composition, Fluent UI v9 (tokens, icons, dark mode), and the `@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` package shape.</role>

  <goal>3 new action buttons render per item in order (Check / Remove / Keep / existing Add-to-To-Do). Clicking each invokes the corresponding hook handler from task 030. Optimistic UI updates as expected. Toasts confirm. Dark mode + light mode both render correctly per ADR-021. `DailyBriefingApp.smoke.test.tsx` passes with `sprk_briefingstate` fixture updates.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-4, FR-5, FR-6, FR-7: the widget UI surfaces the 3 new actions with Fluent v9 icons and standard Spaarke button patterns. The UI layer is thin â€” buttons call hook handlers (task 030) which do the work. Owner-specified icons: `CheckmarkRegular` (Check), `DismissRegular` (Remove), `CalendarAddRegular` (Keep +7d). ADR-024: the existing "Add to To Do" 4th button MUST remain functional â€” `useInlineTodoCreate` with `TODO_REGARDING_CATALOG` preserved.
    </background>
